documentation.text:
@dev Adds a key-value pair to a map, or updates the value for an existing
 key. O(1).
 Returns true if the key was added to the map, that is if it was not
 already present.

@dev Removes a key-value pair from a map. O(1).
 Returns true if the key was removed from the map, that is if it was present.

documentation.text:
@dev Returns the key-value pair stored at position `index` in the map. O(1).
 Note that there are no guarantees on the ordering of entries inside the
 array, and it may change when more entries are added or removed.
 Requirements:
 - `index` must be strictly less than {length}.

natspec.details: Library for managing an enumerable variant of Solidity's https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types.html#mapping-types[`mapping`] type. Maps have the following properties: - Entries are added, removed, and checked for existence in constant time (O(1)). - Entries are enumerated in O(n). No guarantees are made on the ordering. ``` contract Example {     // Add the library methods     using EnumerableMap for EnumerableMap.UintToAddressMap;     // Declare a set state variable     EnumerableMap.UintToAddressMap private myMap; } ``` The following map types are supported: - `uint256 -> address` (`UintToAddressMap`) since v3.0.0 - `address -> uint256` (`AddressToUintMap`) since v4.6.0
